==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Eparterial
<hw>Ep`ar*te"ri*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>ep-</ets> + <ets>arterial</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Anat.)</fld>
<def>Situated upon or above an artery; -- applied esp. to the branches
of the bronchi given off above the point where the pulmonary artery
crosses the bronchus.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Epaule</ent>⟦br⟧
